(x^3 + 8) = x^3 + 2^3 = (x + 2)(x^2 - 2x + 4)
\lim_{x \to -2} \frac{x^3 + 8}{x+2} \quad = \quad \lim_{x \to -2} \frac{(\cancel{x + 2})(x^2 - 2x + 4)}{(\cancel{x + 2})} \quad \overset{x\neq -2}  = \quad\lim_{x\to -2} x^2 - 2x + 4 = 12
